{{As of|2012|4|24}}, '''Barack Obama's Twitter account''' ('''@BarackObama''') is the eighth most popular official celebrity Twitter account.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/music-news/9125284/Lady-Gaga-breaks-Twitter-record.html |title=Lady Gaga breaks Twitter record |publisher=Telegraph |accessdate=24 April 2012}}</ref> It is the official [[Twitter]] account for [[United States President]] [[Barack Obama]] (as designated by the verified icon next to his name), although he also tweets through @whitehouse. He has ranked at least as high as fourth in terms of followers.<ref name="SinghDiamond2012">{{cite book|author1=Shiv Singh|author2=Stephanie Diamond|title=Social Media Marketing For Dummies|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=0Dnv9AZ8Tj4C&pg=PA143|accessdate=26 April 2012|date=3 April 2012|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=978-1-118-06514-3|pages=143<U+2013>}}</ref> The account is "run by #Obama2012 campaign staff. Tweets from the President are signed -bo."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/#!/BarackObama|title=Barack Obama|accessdate=2012-05-26|publisher=[[Twitter]]}}</ref> On May 24, 2012, Obama became the first President to respond to questions on Twitter.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/whitehouse/status/205772255966396416|title=@whitehouse status|accessdate=26 May 2012|date=24 May 2012|publisher=[[Twitter]]|author=Obama, Barack}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/05/24/barack-obama-twitter-chat_n_1544215.html|title=Barack Obama Twitter Chat: President Answers Questions On Twitter|accessdate=26 May 2012|date=24 May 2012|work=[[Huffington Post]]|author=Klapper, Ethan}}</ref>

